  "title": "Valkyrien Skies + Supplementaries Cannon Fix",
  "description": "Fixes aiming mode! - A few simple patches for Valkyrien Skies 2 and Supplementaries cannons.",
  "body": "<div style=\"background-image: linear-gradient(#4281B6 0px, #4281B6 120px, #91BEE5 240px, #91BEE5 400px, transparent 501px); text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block;\" src=\"https://media.forgecdn.net/attachments/description/1265947/description_6c5f306f-d8d8-43a1-9181-4c411af4d211.png\" alt=\"Title Card\" width=\"100%\" height=\"283\">\n<div style=\"font-family: Segoe UI, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: center; font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6;\"><img style=\"border: 6px solid #D6A33A;\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/J2goeKD.gif\" alt=\"Loading preview GIF...\" width=\"760\"><br><br>\n<h2 style=\"color: #ffd46a;\">Intent of This Mod</h2>\n<p><span style=\"color: #fff;\">Supplementaries cannonballs now detect and damage Valkyrien Skies 2 ships.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #fff;\">Cannon aiming mode works when the cannon is assembled onto a ship.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #fff;\">Works with your Supplementaries cannon config.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<hr>\n<h2 style=\"color: #ffd46a;\">&nbsp;</h2>\n<h2 style=\"color: #ffd46a;\">Tested Versions</h2>\n<p><span style=\"color: #fff;\"><em>Tested as of <strong>06/02/2026 &nbsp;</strong></em></span>&rarr; &nbsp;<strong style=\"color: #ffd46a;\">2.0.1&nbsp;</strong> &rarr;&nbsp; <strong style=\"color: #ffd46a;\">VS2 1.20-2.4.11&nbsp;</strong> &rarr;&nbsp; <strong style=\"color: #ffd46a;\">Supplementaries 1.20-3.1.43</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<hr>\n<h2 style=\"color: #ffd46a;\">&nbsp;</h2>\n<h2 style=\"color: #ffd46a;\">⚠ Incompatibilities ⚠</h2>\n<p><span style=\"color: #fff;\">See the VS2 compatibility page <span style=\"color: #3598db;\"><a style=\"color: #3598db;\" href=\"https://wiki.valkyrienskies.org/wiki/Compatibility_list\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">here</a></span>.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #fff;\">This mod uses <strong>Mixins</strong> on Supplementaries classes. </span><span style=\"color: #fff;\">Any mod that depends on those classes may be incompatible.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<hr>\n<h2 style=\"color: #ffd46a;\">&nbsp;</h2>\n<h2 style=\"color: #ffd46a;\"><span style=\"color: #f1c40f;\">Modpack Permissions</span></h2>\n<p><span style=\"color: #fff;\">Feel free to use this in your modpack as long as it properly links back to this project for downloads.</span></p>\n</div>\n<div style=\"font-family: Segoe UI, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: center; font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6;\">&nbsp;</div>\n<div style=\"font-family: Segoe UI, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: center; font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6;\">&nbsp;</div>\n<div style=\"font-family: Segoe UI, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: center; font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6;\"><br>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #f1c40f;\">Enjoy! 😁</span></h2>\n</div>\n</div>",
